configset listname maxlength = [VALUE]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value : 40000
Data Type     : integer
Category      : moderate
Password Notes: Visible only with password. 
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset listname maxlength = 40000


Sets the maximum size of an unapproved message in number of characters.
Set to zero to disable the message length check. Actual message size
and a boolean for exceeding this limit can be tested in access_rules.


See Also:
   help configset access_rules           (how to trap violations of this limit)
   help configset access_rules_variables (for what to test in access_rules)

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
